<TEXT>
a small plane plunged nosefirst into a 
freshly plowed field during heavy rain tuesday sinking so deep in 
mud and water that neither the wreckage nor its occupants could be 
found authorities said 
it hit and didnt bounce jump or anything dr wesley dyer 
the rapides parish coroner said after walking from the muddy field 
where the wreckage was found i think a thunderhead twisted it up 
and spit out the pieces 
the crash happened sometime tuesday afternoon and the plane 
could seat four people but authorities still hadnt found any 
bodies by tuesday night because the plane was so deeply submerged 
in the waterfilled hole 
small pieces of the plane were visible over about a 100yard 
area in the field located between us 71 and a rural road just 
northwest of this small central louisiana community 
firemen city police and parish sheriffs deputies were still 
trying tuesday night to drain the hole containing the plane so the 
wreckage could be pulled out 
authorities said it probably would be morning before they would 
learn whether anyone had been killed 
dyer said a small piece of wing with a serial number on it was 
found in the field and the number was given to the federal aviation 
administration for tracing 
</TEXT>
