this case mr gorbachev the president has a record of encouraging 
or certainly acquiescing in the peaceful evolution in eastern 
europe he has demonstrated that he is committed to peaceful 
change and the evolution of democracy 
mulroney said he agreed with bush that gorbachev represents a 
new kind of soviet leader more attractive and more realistic 
and appears to be much more in keeping with some if not all of 
the values that we in the west defend 
he said the soviet leader had displayed reasonableness that we 
had not come to know in earlier soviet leaders 
earlier on his plane bush said there was an awful lot to be 
done on arms control in advance of his meeting with gorbachev 
and said i cant predict how much will be done by the time the 
summit rolls around 
he said it was a good thing to have a date set and obviously 
this will serve as a bit of a catalyst or goal for getting things 
done 
he said he didnt want to suggest were going to have all the 
details worked out by the time of the summit 
you deal with whats on the table bush said 
the superpowers are negotiating agreements on longrange nuclear 
weapons chemical arms and troop and tank levels in europe 
bush said combining the baseball game between the toronto blue 
jays and the texas rangers with the mulroney meeting just seemed 
like a wonderful way to do it the presidents son george walker 
bush is part owner of the rangers 
the meeting with mulroney is the first in a series of talks bush 
plans this month with western leaders before the summit in 
washington 
bush will fly to bermuda on friday to meet with british prime 
minister margaret thatcher and will hold talks with french 
president francois mitterrand in key largo fla on april 19 
the president enjoys a strong friendship with mulroney the 
prime minister and his family were guests last year at the bush 
seaside vacation home in kennebunkport maine 
