the first free elections in east germanys 41 years were held 
march 18 an alliance of conservative parties favoring quick 
reunification with west germany won 48 percent of the vote for 193 
seats in the 400seat parliament and began negotiating to form a 
coalition 
christian democrat leader lothar de maiziere was charged by 
parliament to form a new government he is building a broad 
coalition with the social democrats which will enable him to must 
the twothirds majority needed to make the constitutional changes 
