<TEXT>
poland 
the oncebanned solidarity free trade union won overwhelmingly 
over the communist party in partially democratic elections last 
june that were agreed upon at historic negotiations between the 
trade union and communist leadership 
in september solidarity formed the first government in eastern 
europe not dominated by communists under premier tadeusz 
mazowiecki a solidarity activist and journalist 
following the trend begun in hungary the old communist party 
dissolved itself in jaunary and a new social democracy party was 
formed 
the 23member cabinet includes 12 solidarity members the others 
are former members of the nowdissolved communist party or of the 
peasant party and the democratic party 
president gen wojciech jaruzelski a now unaffiliated former 
communist elected by parliament in july for a sixyear term his is 
