<TEXT>
conservative leader constantine mitsotakis 
received a mandate to form a government today after working out a 
deal with a small party to clinch a onevote parliamentary majority 
mitsotakis head of the new democracy party that won half of 
parliaments seats in an election sunday said his government would 
be sworn in on wednesday 
the party wants to liberalize the inflationplagued economy 
slash the government deficit and attract foreign investment 
after a onehour meeting with president christos sartzetakis 
the 71yearold mitsotakis told reporters i dont have much to 
say as you know i met with mr sartzetakis who gave me a mandate 
to form a government 
miksotakis received the mandate after he assured sartzetakis 
that he controlled 151 of the 300 seats in parliament after 
sundays elections new democracy won 150 seats in the balloting 
then received the support of rightist costis stephanopoulos whose 
renewal party won one seat 
stephanopoulos said monday he offered the vote of his lone 
victorious candidate without preconditions and that he would 
not be a member of the government which will be an allnew 
democracy cabinet 
his support broke an impasse that had gripped greek politics 
since inconclusive elections last june and november 
temporary governments since the socialists were voted out in 
june have been largely ineffective in dealing with the economy 
saddled with 17 percent inflation and a 156 billion government 
deficit 
a new democracy victory could also mean greece will make 
longpostponed decisions on a us extradition request for a 
palestinian wanted for the 1982 bombing of an airliner over hawaii 
and on a new military bases agreement with the united states 
mitsotakis has said greeces defense depends heavily on the four 
us military bases which are to close by november unless a new 
agreement is reached he has also said that he would extradite 
mohammed rashid the palestinian wanted by the united states 
the athens stock exchange reacted favorably to the conservative 
victory new democracy has promised to cut government spending 
streamline the public sector and reduce government intervention in 
the economy 
the exchange posted a 148 percent overall gain in hectic 
trading on monday and a 66 percent gain at the close on tuesday 
according to the general index 
the first task of the newly elected lawmakers who convene april 
23 wil be to elect a president to replace sartzetakis whose term 
has expired 
