we propose that eastwest consultations begin on rules to 
govern the transfer of dualpurpose technology said sitarian 
referring to technology that can be used for both military and 
civilian purposes 
cocom stands for the 17nation coordinating committee for 
multilateral export controls 
the cocom nations are working on proposals for loosening 
restrictions on technology sales to reforming eastern european 
countries however the united states has indicated it will take a 
tougher stand on technology sales to the soviet union 
sitarian said moscow considered the bonn meeting a major 
milestone in the process of intensified eastwest cooperation 
that began with the helsinki conference on security and cooperation 
in europe in 1975 
he said we seek to integrate ourselves into the world economy 
in a dynamic fashion and on a large scale and added the soviets 
want an open type of economy 
he also said changes at home and abroad bring us closer to a 
key objective namely the convertibility of the ruble but he did 
not elaborate 
economic experts from the 35 nations have been meeting in bonn 
since march 19 to examine ways of improving eastwest cooperation 
and helping with the reconstruction of eastern europe 
the bonn conference ends on wednesday 
