<TEXT>
the fbi on tuesday awarded its first medal of 
valor to agent edmundo mireles jr who was severely wounded in a 
miami shootout and later joined a classaction lawsuit accusing the 
bureau of discrimination against hispanics 
mireles and fellow agents were involved in a shootout outside 
