international accord to support freemarket economic policies the 
soviet economy is now stalled somewhere between central planning 
and free markets 
on tuesday the soviets asked the western nations in bonn for 
the conference on economic cooperation in europe to ease limits on 
the sale of hightechnology goods to the soviet union 
