the communist partys policymaking central 
committee accused a radical faction on tuesday of trying to split 
the party and indicated its members could be expelled 
it said in its statement that the democratic platform a group 
that includes populist boris n yeltsin historian yuri afanasiev 
and economist gavriil popov was trying to turn the party into a 
formless association with full freedom for factions and groups 
that is to actually break it apart 
the democratic platform seeks faster and deeper political and 
economic reforms than president mikhail s gorbachev 
the time has come when it is necessary to work out what to 
do with those party members who are persistently and purposefully 
leading affairs to a break the statement said can these kinds 
of people really remain in the ranks of the communist party of the 
soviet union 
a party congress begins july 2 the party is trying to prevent 
more splits after party members in the baltic republics of 
lithuania and estonia decided to break away and form independent 
parties 
