january whether to break with the national communist party to form 
a social democratic party 
such a split could be more serious than the break with the 
baltic parties some of the most progressive party members from 
across the soviet union would likely join the breakaway group 
thereby forming a nationwide opposition 
the statement of the 248member central committee a body that 
includes all major party leaders said party organizations must 
decide whether individual democratic platform members should remain 
in the party 
gorbachev who is both president and party leader has pushed 
the communists to accept a multiparty system but at the same time 
has tried to prevent a split among its 19 million members he says 
party unity is necessary to carry out his reform plan 
tuesdays central committee attack came days after the party in 
the byelorussian republic which is known for its conservatism 
gave local party organizations the power to expel members of the 
democratic platform 
in an interview with the national daily selskaya zhizn published 
