mcmartin buckey was acquitted of 12 charges but prosecutors 
decided to retry buckey on eight counts unresolved by the jury 
jurors deadlocked on 13 charges but the prosecution dropped five 
the first trial of buckey and his mother lasted nearly three 
years and cost 13 million making it the longest costliest 
criminal trial in us history 
