if convicted 
kraft 25 faces five counts of aggravated murder while 
johnson 36 is charged with conspiracy to commit murder 
prosecutors in ohio have alleged that the averys who also 
belonged to lundgrens cult were killed as part of a cleansing 
sacrifice before group members left the kirtland farm on wilderness 
treks in other states 
their capture ended a nationwide manhunt on jan 34 the bodies 
of the avery family were found buried under a barn on the rented 
farm where the group lived communestyle in kirtland about 30 
miles east of cleveland 
authorities in lake county ohio have until april 20 to pick up 
the defendants and return them 
defense attorneys had filed legal challenges to the extradition 
but they were denied by a state appeals court last week 
lundgrens attorney militza durovic sought a review by the 
state supreme court but told the judge that she had received no 
response 
lundgrens return could be postponed if the high court issues a 
stay of extradition before he leaves san diego but durovic 
acknowledged outside court that such a ruling was a long shot 
attorneys for johnson and kraft did not seek a supreme court review 
lundgren his wife alice 38 and 19yearold son damon were 
arrested jan 7 in a san diegoarea motel room near the mexican 
border kraft of nauvoo ill and johnson of holden mo were 
arrested jan 10 
damon lundgren was returned to ohio last week after legal 
challenges to his extradition failed he has pleaded innocent to 
five counts each of aggravated murder and kidnapping 
alice lundgren waived extradition shortly after her arrest and 
was returned voluntarily to ohio in late january she has pleaded 
innocent to five counts each of complicity conspiracy and 
kidnapping 
jeffrey lundgren also had been a tour guide at the kirtland 
