reservation casinos last summer but found him innocent of a more 
serious felony charge 
the us district court jury acquitted kakwirakeron 47 of 
using a deadly or dangerous weapon to turn back fbi agents and did 
not consider another felony charge of using a firearm in commission 
of a crime 
kakwirakeron also known as arthur montour was convicted of 
conspiracy and forcibly impeding the execution of federal search 
warrants during the july 20 raid at the st regis reservation 
kakwirakeron faces up to three years in prison and a 5000 
fine sentencing was set for june 12 
the verdict came during the first full day of deliberations 
after jurors listened to nearly four hours of testimony by the 
defendant and four state police investigators 
in closing arguments monday assistant us attorney john duncan 
