of nearly 11 million gallons of north slope crude oil from the 
tanker exxon valdez which ran aground and ripped its bottom open 
on a charted reef outside shipping lanes in prince william sound 
the oil coated hundreds of miles of coastline and killed 
countless fish birds and other marine life 
