traded his 1979 volkswagon for the ownership rights to a telephone 
line a sao paulo housewife swapped a spare color television set 
for a used stove 
neighbors trade rice eggs or meat for deodorant shampoo or 
other items with unfrozen prices 
tens of thousands of amazon prospectors see their dreams dashed 
because the price of gold is plunging penniless miners are leaving 
the jungle to seek work in cities where there is none 
