sao paulo no replies 
i knew it would be difficult to sell my car but this is 
ridiculous she said im asking half what i paid 
cira cochenga owns a ceramics shop in the outskirts of sao paulo 
and has several months of orders backed up but no cash to pay her 
10 employees or buy supplies 
my clients want to pay me with old money cruzados but i need 
cruzeiros for production said ms cochenga 39 who quit a 
teaching job to open the business with her sister in 1986 its 
so frustrating im about ready to go dig up clay in my backyard 
unions say more than 200000 brazilians have been dismissed 
because employers have no money to pay them either because of 
blocked funds or low sales 
general motors gave 18000 workers 18 days paid leave because 
the demand for cars has evaporated another 40000 auto workers in 
brazil were laid off with pay indefinitely ane 160000 were 
required to take vacations early 
