union in illinois 
its important for children to have an appreciation of their 
own individuality as well as the constitutional values that protect 
that individuality she said orthodoxy in apparel is not 
something a school board should be involved in 
requiring uniforms might also pose a financial hurdle for the 
poor whicher said but some families are applauding the trend 
parents seem to really like the idea said shel erlich a 
spokesman for the los angeles unified school district the nations 
