<TEXT>
ten years ago eugeny bragarnik gave up on 
soviet promises of a workers paradise to pursue the american dream 
bragarnik started out as a cab driver he now owns a restaurant 
and a threebedroom house drives an audi has a son in college 
jogs five miles a day on a seaside boardwalk and loves threes 
company reruns on cable 
he has little interest in soviet upheaval even if the communist 
monopoly of seven decades is ending lithuania leads restive 
republics seeking independence armenians war with azerbaijanis 
and eastern bloc tyrants have tumbled like the berlin wall 
i dont think about that government its past its gone 
said bragarnik everything i have is over here my soul is here 
most of the time i am thinking about this government 
at bragarniks odessa restaurant nestled among the delis and 
