<TEXT>
gazelle microcircuits inc has become 
the first company to receive funding under a new department of 
defense program that allows the department to get a return on its 
investment 
gazelle will receive 4 million from the pentagons defense 
advanced research projects agency darpa to develop 
ultrahighspeed data communications projects 
the agency which is the defense departments central research 
and development branch is attempting to expand its role in helping 
deveop domestic industries involved in critical technologies 
in exchange gazelle will pay darpa a return similar to that 
received by venture capitalists for investments in companies with 
important technologies 
in 12 months the agency can decide either to take royalties on 
sales of the products developed under the agreement or payments 
based on the appreciation of gazelles stock 
we believe it will help us and other future recipients develop 
technology critical to us defense needs and also speed 
development of technology vital to us commercial 
competitiveness jerry r crowley gazelles president and chief 
executive officer said of the agreement 
in the past darpa has funded several other research and 
production projects however the agreement with gazelle is the 
first under the agencys newly granted authority to support such 
activities by means other than traditional grants and contracts 
according to gazelle 
gazelle produces siliconcompatible integrated circuits based on 
gallium arsenide 
under the darpa agreement gazelle will design and make gallium 
arsenide chips and subsystems operating at 1 gigabit per second and 
faster which will allow computers talk to each other as quickly as 
they operate internally the company said this capability is vital 
for highresolution graphics highdefinition television parallel 
processing and distributed computing 
