<TEXT>
fortytwo nations have agreed on the terms of a 
development bank for eastern europe after reaching a compromise 
over the role of the soviet union 
under the compromise the soviet union will become a 
fullfledged member of the european bank for reconstruction and 
development but has agreed to limit its borrowing for the first 
three years 
the official signing of an accord to create the bank will take 
place may 30 in paris said jacques attali advisor to french 
president francois mitterrand the location of the bank 
headquarters and its first president will be disclosed then he 
said 
attalis announcement followed meetings sunday and monday of 
representatives of the 42 countries planning to contribute to the 
banks capital base plans call for the bank to have a capital base 
of 10 billion european currency units the equivalent of about 12 
billion 
the united states would contribute 10 percent of the banks 
capital while the european community would be responsible for 3 
percent france the united kingdom west germany italy and japan 
each will contribute 85 percent with the rest spread out among 
the other members ec countries collectively will account for 51 
percent of the capital contribution 
the soviet union will contribute 6 percent of the banks 
capital he said 
the representatives agreed on 58 articles of the banks 
statutes including the type of currency to be used in the bank and 
the amount and form of capital contributions of each member attali 
said 
for the first three years the soviet union will only be 
eligible for loans totalling the amount of paidin capital it 
contributes each year attali said after that period the 
restrictions can be removed with the approval of 85 percent of the 
member countries he said 
the delegates agreed that the us dollar japanese yen and 
european currency unit all can be used to contribute capital to the 
bank 
at the first session to set terms for the bank in january the 
united states objected to full participation by the soviet union 
unless moscow initiated major market reforms 
in addition to the united states and virtually every european 
country participants in the bank include japan morocco israel 
egypt and south korea 
