readers digest association inc said tuesday 
that its french subsidiary plans to launch a monthly magazine in 
october that will be designed to help families manage their 
finances 
it would be the first family finance magazine from the publisher 
of readers digest and the first magazine startup for the company 
since its stock was made available to the public for the first time 
in midfebruary 
readers digest association said the new magazine will be called 
budgets famille or family budgets and will contain news feature 
articles and tips on topics ranging from savings and borrowing 
strategies to the best ways families can budget for their 
childrens education and vacations 
the company which is based in pleasantville ny has been 
publishing a french language edition of readers digest since 1947 
and that magazine called selection has a circulation of 11 
million a month 
weve designed our new magazine to be of service to readers 
in the same tradition as readers digest henri capdeville 
managing director of readers digest france was quoted in a news 
release 
he said while there are other magazines published in france that 
focus on personal finances and investments none cover the combined 
topics of families and money 
the magazines target audience will be upper and middleincome 
readers between 30 and 45 years old 
bruce trachtenberg a spokesman for readers digest in 
pleasantville said the parent company intends to see how well it 
performs in france before deciding whether to publish versions of 
the new french magazine in other languages and other countries 
but he noted that the company said when describing its business 
