microsofts industrystandard msdos 
computer software can now say it in cyrillic 
microsoft introduced a russianlanguage version of its msdos 
operating system monday msdos is the standard base layer of 
software for ibm personal computers and compatible models and is 
installed on more than 40 million computers worldwide 
the system now comes in 13 languages 
the new russianlanguage version further underscores our 
commitment to the international marketplace which is now 
responsible for 53 percent of our revenues said bill gates 
microsofts chairman 
the russian version uses cyrillic characters onscreen and also 
runs printers with cyrillic typefaces 
the translation is the first in russian by microsoft it was 
done with the help of dialogue a sovietamerican computer joint 
venture formed in 1988 
an operating system is the base layer of software that controls 
such computer functions as operating the keyboard and opening 
files it differs from applications programs which provide such 
specific uses as word processing or spreadsheets 
the standardization of soviet computer science on the 
worldwide dos standard opens the door for our users to the largest 
application base in the world said priotr zvelov the soviet 
chairman of dialogue it also allows our developers to build 
applications for a worldwide market 
